It's a fantastic league.

495
00:22:29.884 --> 00:22:33.347
And the television deal
allows it to survive.

496
00:22:33.382 --> 00:22:35.316
you know. in terms
of being able to pay

497
00:22:35.351 --> 00:22:36.757
the salaries they're paying.

498
00:22:38.794 --> 00:22:40.629
- [Reporter] But it will
get a rude awakening.

499
00:22:40.664 --> 00:22:43.434
- It'll get a rude awakening
somewhere along. yeah.

500
00:22:43.469 --> 00:22:45.964
- We do realize that we
have something to prove.

501
00:22:45.999 --> 00:22:48.769
We will be playing our hearts
out tomorrow for our fans.

502
00:22:48.804 --> 00:22:50.397
our country. and ourselves.

503
00:22:50.432 --> 00:22:52.905
and hopefully. we'll come
away with the right result.

504
00:22:55.547 --> 00:22:58.548
- Are you at all
concerned that you've lost

505
00:22:58.583 --> 00:23:00.913
a bit of sympathy with
England supporters

506
00:23:00.948 --> 00:23:03.113
after the events of this week?

507
00:23:03.148 --> 00:23:05.247
- Once we step onto
that pitch. you know.

508
00:23:05.282 --> 00:23:07.491
they'll realize and they'll
see in the boys' faces

509
00:23:07.526 --> 00:23:10.120
that. you know.
everything's behind us.

510
00:23:10.155 --> 00:23:12.320
and we want England to do well.

511
00:23:12.355 --> 00:23:15.026
- You don't think this
pampered millionaire image

512
00:23:15.061 --> 00:23:18.667
that has been put about has
slightly rebounded on you?

513
00:23:18.702 --> 00:23:20.834
The. "Who the hell do you
think you are?" Headlines.

514
00:23:20.869 --> 00:23:21.967
That kind of thing?

515
00:23:23.575 --> 00:23:25.509
- No. because I think that

516
00:23:25.544 --> 00:23:27.907
them headlines will
probably always be there.

517
00:23:27.942 --> 00:23:30.514
whilst. you know. the
wages are what they are.

518
00:23:30.549 --> 00:23:32.549
But you know. to be honest.

519
00:23:32.584 --> 00:23:34.243
that's always going to
be there. as I said.

520
00:23:34.278 --> 00:23:38.786
So. you know. we're prepared
to take the criticism.

521
00:23:38.821 --> 00:23:41.085
because you know. we've
put ourselves out there.

522
00:23:41.120 --> 00:23:44.594
and we're well
prepared to take that.

523
00:23:44.629 --> 00:23:46.563
But once we're on the pitch.

524
00:23:46.598 --> 00:23:48.829
people realize how
much football does mean

525
00:23:48.864 --> 00:23:50.325
to every one of us.

526
00:23:50.360 --> 00:23:52.767
And after the World
Cup. you know.

527
00:23:52.802 --> 00:23:54.967
I had to come away and do well.

528
00:23:55.002 --> 00:23:56.639
and do well that season.

529
00:23:56.674 --> 00:23:59.004
And I felt I did. and
I've come on from there.

530
00:24:00.238 --> 00:24:01.743
and it's made me
a stronger person.

531
00:24:09.478 --> 00:24:10.851
- [Commentator] Beckham
could raise the roof here

532
00:24:10.886 --> 00:24:11.687
with a goal.

533
00:24:13.559 --> 00:24:15.658
I don't believe it.

534
00:24:15.693 --> 00:24:20.157
David Beckham scores
the goal to take England

535
00:24:20.192 --> 00:24:23.028
all the way to the
World Cup finals.

536
00:24:24.570 --> 00:24:26.295
Give that man a knighthood.

537
00:24:27.639 --> 00:24:29.397
- Obviously. you
know. World Cup.

538
00:24:30.675 --> 00:24:32.906
we all know that anything
can happen once you're there.

539
00:24:32.941 --> 00:24:35.678
You've got to have a
certain amount of luck.

540
00:24:35.713 --> 00:24:38.043
And obviously people are
saying that it is too early

541
00:24:38.078 --> 00:24:40.815
for this team to go and
win a major competition.

542
00:24:40.850 --> 00:24:43.114
But I don't feel like it is.

543
00:24:44.986 --> 00:24:46.953
- [Narrator] With Beckham's
career on the rise.

544
00:24:46.988 --> 00:24:49.384
it seemed as though
nothing would stop him.

545
00:24:49.419 --> 00:24:53.894
both as an illusive right-winger
and as a media powerhouse.

546
00:24:53.929 --> 00:24:57.667
Having qualified for the group
stages. spirits were high.

547
00:24:58.769 --> 00:25:00.637
- You know. I feel
that we can go there.

548
00:25:00.672 --> 00:25:04.740
and if we get through the first
stages of the competition.

549
00:25:04.775 --> 00:25:07.336
then I feel that
anything can happen.

550
00:25:08.614 --> 00:25:10.878
- [Narrator] With a new
manager. Sven-Goran Eriksson.

551
00:25:13.443 --> 00:25:15.718
and new captain David Beckham.

552
00:25:15.753 --> 00:25:20.118
2002 looked like the
year football would
finally come home.

553
00:25:20.153 --> 00:25:21.119
- Yes.

554
00:25:21.154 --> 00:25:24.595
(crowd chanting)

555
00:25:24.630 --> 00:25:26.289
- [Man] Absolutely fantastic.

556
00:25:26.324 --> 00:25:28.599
It's the best day of my life.

557
00:25:28.634 --> 00:25:31.195
- [Narrator] But
then. disaster struck.

558
00:25:33.771 --> 00:25:36.739
Whilst playing for Man United
in a Champions League game

559
00:25:36.774 --> 00:25:39.170
against Deportivo La Coruna.

560
00:25:39.205 --> 00:25:43.108
Beckham broke the
second metatarsal
bone in his left foot.

561
00:25:43.143 --> 00:25:46.276
injuring him for the
remainder of the season.

562
00:25:46.311 --> 00:25:48.784
(somber music)

563
00:25:50.282 --> 00:25:51.688
- Well. the metatarsal bones

564
00:25:51.723 --> 00:25:53.756
are some of the major load
bearing bones in the foot.

565
00:25:53.791 --> 00:25:55.692
So if he's broken or
fractured one of those.

566
00:25:55.727 --> 00:25:57.452
and we see the
metatarsal bone here.

567
00:25:57.487 --> 00:25:58.926
flashing in red on the screen.

568
00:25:58.961 --> 00:26:00.763
that means he's going to
be unable to take weight

569
00:26:00.798 --> 00:26:02.193
through the bone or
through the foot.

570
00:26:02.228 --> 00:26:04.635
And if you can't do that. you
certainly can't play football.

571
00:26:04.670 --> 00:26:06.769
- I had a stress fracture
in the fifth metatarsal

572
00:26:06.804 --> 00:26:07.671
of my left foot.

573
00:26:09.268 --> 00:26:11.906
I did it in a
game. just running.

574
00:26:11.941 --> 00:26:13.644
It just broke down.

575
00:26:13.679 --> 00:26:16.075
and it took me
three months exactly

576
00:26:16.110 --> 00:26:17.813
to come back. playing.

577
00:26:17.848 --> 00:26:19.012
- Very difficult to
say at this minute.

578
00:26:19.047 --> 00:26:21.212
We're not too sure the
type of fracture he has.

579
00:26:21.247 --> 00:26:23.445
but if all goes well
and the bone heals up

580
00:26:23.480 --> 00:26:24.754
within the eight weeks.

581
00:26:24.789 --> 00:26:26.789
he's still going to be missing
a lot of match fitness.

582
00:26:26.824 --> 00:26:28.692
So I would imagine
he'll probably miss

583
00:26:28.727 --> 00:26:31.387
the opening group stages.
but if he does come back.

584
00:26:31.422 --> 00:26:33.092
we'll probably see him
initially coming in.

585
00:26:33.127 --> 00:26:34.731
playing a substitute role.

586
00:26:40.200 --> 00:26:41.430
- What I think about that?

587
00:26:41.465 --> 00:26:42.838
- [Reporter] You think
it can have any effect?

588
00:26:42.873 --> 00:26:45.434
- If it has an effect.
please do it. all of you.

589
00:26:45.469 --> 00:26:47.711
(all laughing)

590
00:26:47.746 --> 00:26:50.241
- The whole business of
The Sun calling for people

591
00:26:50.276 --> 00:26:51.638
to pray for Beckham.

592
00:26:51.673 --> 00:26:55.312
I hope. hope it's
an elaborate joke.

593
00:26:55.347 --> 00:26:58.414
because if it isn't.
then we are all doomed.

594
00:27:00.792 --> 00:27:03.122
- [Sven] After the
session he had today.

595
00:27:03.157 --> 00:27:07.896
he felt very well. no
complaints. no pain at all.

596
00:27:07.931 --> 00:27:09.799
So that's very positive.

597
00:27:09.834 --> 00:27:11.394
- Hopefully this week.

598
00:27:11.429 --> 00:27:13.429
it would be great to welcome
a few of the players back

599
00:27:13.464 --> 00:27:16.003
onto the training pitch. and
hopefully. David's one of them.

600
00:27:16.038 --> 00:27:20.634
- [Alex] David's slim.
tall. angular. human being.

601
00:27:20.669 --> 00:27:23.439
Natural fit boy.
natural athlete.

602
00:27:23.474 --> 00:27:25.342
Beckham's natural.

603
00:27:25.377 --> 00:27:27.718
So. after his metatarsal injury.

604
00:27:27.753 --> 00:27:30.886
I was very confident that
David would no problem

605
00:27:30.921 --> 00:27:32.723
going to the World Cup.

606
00:27:32.758 --> 00:27:34.351
- [Narrator] A determined
Beckham worked hard

607
00:27:34.386 --> 00:27:36.287
to get back from injury in time

608
00:27:36.322 --> 00:27:39.488
for the opening group stage
game of the competition.

609
00:27:39.523 --> 00:27:40.764
- [Reporter] How's the foot?

610
00:27:40.799 --> 00:27:42.392
- [David] It's a lot
better. A lot better.

611
00:27:42.427 --> 00:27:45.164
I run for the first
time two days ago.

612
00:27:45.199 --> 00:27:46.968
on Saturday morning.

613
00:27:47.003 --> 00:27:51.467
and it was a little bit achy
after. but it's not a problem.

614
00:27:51.502 --> 00:27:52.809
- [Reporter] How is
the x-ray looking?

615
00:27:52.844 --> 00:27:55.240
What are the United
physios saying about this?

616
00:27:55.275 --> 00:27:57.275
- Well. the callus is
forming around the bone.

617
00:27:57.310 --> 00:27:59.882
So. that's the best sign.

618
00:27:59.917 --> 00:28:01.752
Surgeons are really
happy with it.

619
00:28:01.787 --> 00:28:04.854
They've been looking after
me for the last four weeks.

620
00:28:04.889 --> 00:28:08.891
watching it. and it's
really. really come on a lot.

621
00:28:08.926 --> 00:28:11.190
And United physios have
been watching obviously.

622
00:28:11.225 --> 00:28:13.093
and so it's really quite good.

623
00:28:13.128 --> 00:28:16.624
- Metatarsals mended. and
old injuries forgotten.

624
00:28:16.659 --> 00:28:20.463
the air around the team and
their supporters is optimistic.

625
00:28:20.498 --> 00:28:21.662
- I'm feeling confident.

626
00:28:21.697 --> 00:28:22.806
Now we've got
David Beckham back.

627
00:28:22.841 --> 00:28:24.841
that's got to be a
very big positive.

628
00:28:28.913 --> 00:28:30.473
- [Narrator] With
Beckham back from injury.

629
00:28:30.508 --> 00:28:32.882
his dreams of revenge
against the Argentines

630
00:28:32.917 --> 00:28:35.115
were closer than ever.

631
00:28:35.150 --> 00:28:38.052
When England drew Argentina
in the group stage

632
00:28:38.087 --> 00:28:39.185
of the competition.

633
00:28:40.320 --> 00:28:42.122
- And H one for Japan.

634
00:28:43.191 --> 00:28:44.421
Argentina.

635
00:28:46.524 --> 00:28:47.897
England.

636
00:28:47.932 --> 00:28:50.196
- [Narrator] However. not
everyone was optimistic

637
00:28:50.231 --> 00:28:51.725
about the draw.

638
00:28:51.760 --> 00:28:54.431
- With Argentina.
well. it's about time

639
00:28:54.466 --> 00:28:56.004
things turned in favor for us.

640
00:28:56.039 --> 00:28:58.633
So. a bit of luck.
a bit of hard work.

641
00:28:58.668 --> 00:29:01.207
and I think probably
make the most of it.

642
00:29:01.242 --> 00:29:05.343
- Sweden. We've not beaten
them for long time. Sweden.

643
00:29:06.478 --> 00:29:07.818
They're a better team than us.

644
00:29:07.853 --> 00:29:09.215
- When we got Nigeria.

645
00:29:09.250 --> 00:29:11.855
I did think. of all the teams
in Africa. to land Nigeria.

646
00:29:11.890 --> 00:29:13.923
It was completely.
completely unfair.

647
00:29:13.958 --> 00:29:15.254
They're the best team out there.

648
00:29:15.289 --> 00:29:17.894
So we've picked the
best in South America.

649
00:29:17.929 --> 00:29:20.831
the best in Africa. and a
reasonably good European team.

650
00:29:20.866 --> 00:29:22.096
I mean. had we had
France as well.

651
00:29:22.131 --> 00:29:23.757
that really would
have been a bit tough.

652
00:29:23.792 --> 00:29:24.934
- [Reporter] It was
off for some training.

653
00:29:24.969 --> 00:29:27.662
a fairly gentle and
relaxed affair today.

654
00:29:27.697 --> 00:29:30.841
with Beckham sporting the
latest of the Mohicans.

655
00:29:30.876 --> 00:29:34.438
And the news from the camp
is all are fit and well.

656
00:29:34.473 --> 00:29:36.011
- I'm going to watch it now.

657
00:29:36.046 --> 00:29:37.012
- [Reporter] You're on your way?

658
00:29:37.047 --> 00:29:37.914
- Yeah.

659
00:29:37.949 --> 00:29:39.212
- I'm missing the first half.

660
00:29:39.247 --> 00:29:40.741
but I'll see the second
half when I get in.

661
00:29:40.776 --> 00:29:44.514
- England's going to
win about a million nil.

662
00:29:45.715 --> 00:29:47.088
- [Narrator] It wasn't
long before Beckham

663
00:29:47.123 --> 00:29:49.750
was given the chance at revenge.

664
00:29:49.785 --> 00:29:52.291
On the 7th of June. 2002.

665
00:29:52.326 --> 00:29:54.964
England played
Argentina yet again.

666
00:29:54.999 --> 00:29:57.934
when on the stroke of the half
England received a penalty.

667
00:30:00.400 --> 00:30:03.973
(commentator shouting)

668
00:30:04.008 --> 00:30:07.273
- [Narrator] And who else to
take it. other than Beckham?

669
00:30:07.308 --> 00:30:09.803
(heart beat)

670
00:30:26.525 --> 00:30:27.898
- [Commentator] You
can smash them now.

671
00:30:27.933 --> 00:30:30.230
Beckham has scored for England.

672
00:30:30.265 --> 00:30:33.134
44 minutes. and
he's done it again.

673
00:30:33.169 --> 00:30:36.137
(crowd cheering)

674
00:30:36.172 --> 00:30:40.438
David Beckham puts England
in front against Argentina

675
00:30:40.473 --> 00:30:42.044
in Sapporo.

676
00:30:42.079 --> 00:30:43.804
- [Reporter] You
must be very pleased.

677
00:30:43.839 --> 00:30:45.047
- [David] Very. very pleased.

678
00:30:45.082 --> 00:30:46.213
You know.

679
00:30:46.248 --> 00:30:48.083
I think the whole nation
will be pleased tonight.

680
00:30:48.118 --> 00:30:50.448
You know. I think as
a footballing nation.

681
00:30:51.957 --> 00:30:53.187
we've been waiting for this
result for a long time.

682
00:30:53.222 --> 00:30:55.882
I've been waiting for it
for years. but you know.

683
00:30:55.917 --> 00:30:57.455
it means a lot to everyone.

684
00:30:57.490 --> 00:31:00.161
- [Reporter] I was going to
say. how sweet is that for you?

685
00:31:00.196 --> 00:31:02.966
- [David] Well. it's a lot
better than four years ago.

686
00:31:03.001 --> 00:31:04.528
I can tell you that now.

687
00:31:04.563 --> 00:31:07.597
- Absolutely fantastic. It's
the best day of my life.

688
00:31:07.632 --> 00:31:10.072
- Best night of my life.
Absolutely amazing.

689
00:31:10.107 --> 00:31:12.107
I just can't believe it.

690
00:31:12.142 --> 00:31:15.011
We're in Japan. it's the
most amazing country.

691
00:31:15.046 --> 00:31:16.243
The people have been fantastic.

692
00:31:16.278 --> 00:31:18.311
And we've been the Argies. yes.

693
00:31:20.348 --> 00:31:22.051
- [Narrator] Having
solidified his place

694
00:31:22.086 --> 00:31:24.053
as a national team hero.

695
00:31:24.088 --> 00:31:27.188
not everyone was too keen
on the new Mohawk-wearing

696
00:31:27.223 --> 00:31:28.717
designer Becks.

697
00:31:28.752 --> 00:31:30.092
- Fell in love with Victoria.

698
00:31:30.127 --> 00:31:32.226
I think that obviously that
was a big changing point

699
00:31:32.261 --> 00:31:33.788
in his life.

700
00:31:33.823 --> 00:31:35.196
And me being a football man.

701
00:31:36.661 --> 00:31:40.366
I like to see them totally
committed to the team.

702
00:31:40.401 --> 00:31:44.040
and of course that
wind went down a bit.

703
00:31:44.075 --> 00:31:46.977
I always remember one of
the managers saying to me.

704
00:31:47.012 --> 00:31:48.836
"How is it you get
Beckham and Giggsy

705
00:31:48.871 --> 00:31:51.575
to run up and down that
pitch. his wife present.

706
00:31:51.610 --> 00:31:53.742
produce such quality?"

707
00:31:53.777 --> 00:31:57.020
I said. "Because
desire and ability."

708
00:31:57.055 --> 00:32:00.881
And when David went
off that level.

709
00:32:00.916 --> 00:32:05.622
I had to judge whether it
was affecting the performance

710
00:32:05.657 --> 00:32:07.228
of the team.

711
00:32:07.263 --> 00:32:09.197
and also the
control of the team.

712
00:32:09.232 --> 00:32:10.429
- [Narrator]
Following his return

713
00:32:10.464 --> 00:32:12.068
from the metatarsal injury.

714
00:32:12.103 --> 00:32:15.335
Sir Alex Ferguson opted to
go with the second string

715
00:32:15.370 --> 00:32:17.601
right-winger Ole
Gunnar Solskjaer.

716
00:32:19.077 --> 00:32:22.177
- Ole was one of these
rare human beings

717
00:32:22.212 --> 00:32:25.213
that watched every game.
and he took the notes

718
00:32:25.248 --> 00:32:27.281
in every training session.

719
00:32:27.316 --> 00:32:30.515
And it's obviously.
his desire was later on

720
00:32:30.550 --> 00:32:32.352
to be a coach. obviously.

721
00:32:32.387 --> 00:32:34.486
But it's also more than that.

722
00:32:34.521 --> 00:32:38.325
It's about trying to be the
best you possibly can be.

723
00:32:38.360 --> 00:32:39.986
and giving yourself
the best chance.

724
00:32:40.021 --> 00:32:43.099
and taking all the notes down
in the training sessions.

725
00:32:43.134 --> 00:32:45.200
and watching. when he's a sub.

726
00:32:45.235 --> 00:32:50.238
I used to say to the
substitutes thereafter.

727
00:32:51.571 --> 00:32:54.110
referring to Ole Gunnar
Solskjaer. "Watch the game.

728
00:32:54.145 --> 00:32:55.408
Watch the game.

729
00:32:55.443 --> 00:32:57.971
Don't be having a glance
round at the stadium

730
00:32:58.006 --> 00:33:00.050
or chatting to each
other during the game.

731
00:33:00.085 --> 00:33:02.250
Watch the game." And
that's what Ole did.

732
00:33:03.550 --> 00:33:06.485
- [Reporter] Often said
of you about your temper

733
00:33:06.520 --> 00:33:08.091
and the hairdryer treatment.

734
00:33:08.126 --> 00:33:10.918
you say in the book. "I
had terrible mood storms.

735
00:33:10.953 --> 00:33:13.921
and I would sometimes go home
fearing the consequences."

736
00:33:13.956 --> 00:33:16.022
Do you regret those outbursts?

737
00:33:16.057 --> 00:33:18.629
- No. No. I think
you are who you are.

738
00:33:18.664 --> 00:33:19.597
- [Reporter] What
about the football boot

739
00:33:19.632 --> 00:33:20.829
incident with Beckham?

740
00:33:20.864 --> 00:33:22.369
- [Alex] Yeah.
- [Reporter] That was a

741
00:33:22.404 --> 00:33:23.634
loss of temper. wasn't it?

742
00:33:23.669 --> 00:33:25.570
- Yeah. it was an
accident. yeah.

743
00:33:25.605 --> 00:33:27.803
But it happened. you know?

744
00:33:27.838 --> 00:33:31.972
And I would have
forgotten about.

745
00:33:32.007 --> 00:33:34.150
and the fact it was David.

746
00:33:35.582 --> 00:33:37.615
it was going to end up
the papers. wasn't it?

747
00:33:37.650 --> 00:33:39.188
I mean. there was no way out.

748
00:33:39.223 --> 00:33:41.652
And of course it became a
bit of an issue at the time.

749
00:33:41.687 --> 00:33:42.950
- [Reporter] Though
details were sketchy.

750
00:33:42.985 --> 00:33:44.985
United manager. Alex
Ferguson admitted

751
00:33:45.020 --> 00:33:47.955
he had kicked the boot
accidentally striking Beckham.

752
00:33:47.990 --> 00:33:50.793
At the time. both sides
were keen to play it down.

753
00:33:50.828 --> 00:33:54.269
- [Alex] It was an incident.
which was a freakish...

754
00:33:54.304 --> 00:33:56.205
If I tried it 100 times
or a million times.

755
00:33:56.240 --> 00:33:57.569
it could not happen again.

756
00:33:58.803 --> 00:34:01.375
If I did. I'd have
carried on playing.

757
00:34:01.410 --> 00:34:02.640
He became a great player.

758
00:34:02.675 --> 00:34:05.808
and I think that we've
made the right decision.

759
00:34:05.843 --> 00:34:06.842
in terms of.

760
00:34:08.285 --> 00:34:09.284
you know. when we
go to Real Madrid.

761
00:34:09.319 --> 00:34:11.121
because we felt it was time.

762
00:34:12.322 --> 00:34:13.717
- [Reporter] Being sold
like a piece of meat.

763
00:34:13.752 --> 00:34:15.356
Did that represent your feelings

764
00:34:15.391 --> 00:34:16.687
towards United and
Sir Alex Ferguson?

765
00:34:16.722 --> 00:34:18.656
- I think that I
will miss the fans

766
00:34:18.691 --> 00:34:21.021
and the players that
I've grown up with.

767
00:34:21.056 --> 00:34:24.695
because I've regarded the
players at Manchester United

768
00:34:24.730 --> 00:34:25.630
as my family.

769
00:34:27.205 --> 00:34:29.403
And. you know. I've got a lot
of very special friends there.

770
00:34:29.438 --> 00:34:30.965
A lot of special people.

771
00:34:31.000 --> 00:34:33.407
Everyone's been very
kind to me in Manchester

772
00:34:33.442 --> 00:34:35.178
and looked after
me for 13 years.

773
00:34:35.213 --> 00:34:38.280
And obviously. I'm
sad to leave them.

774
00:34:38.315 --> 00:34:39.908
but you know. I'm
joining Real Madrid.

775
00:34:39.943 --> 00:34:44.946
and that for me is as exciting
as it gets. to be honest.

776
00:34:46.290 --> 00:34:47.586
- I don't think he should go.

777
00:34:47.621 --> 00:34:49.258
I can't understand why they
want to get rid of him.

778
00:34:49.293 --> 00:34:51.788
The lad's totally devoted to
United. He always has been.

779
00:34:51.823 --> 00:34:53.229
And it's not going to
be easy to replace that

780
00:34:53.264 --> 00:34:54.758
with some foreigner.

781
00:34:54.793 --> 00:34:57.299
- I came from Greece
and I want Beckham

782
00:34:57.334 --> 00:34:59.532
to stay in Manchester.

783
00:34:59.567 --> 00:35:00.995
- It would seem on
the surface to be

784
00:35:01.030 --> 00:35:02.997
a very serious
conflict of interest.

785
00:35:03.032 --> 00:35:05.340
Obviously. so much money
is earned by progress

786
00:35:05.375 --> 00:35:06.440
in the Champions League.

787
00:35:06.475 --> 00:35:08.244
and maybe Manchester
United don't believe

788
00:35:08.279 --> 00:35:11.280
they'll play Real Madrid
short of the final.

789
00:35:11.315 --> 00:35:13.282
But the whole thing
is full of oddities.

790
00:35:13.317 --> 00:35:15.042
It's almost as if
Manchester United

791
00:35:15.077 --> 00:35:18.078
have acted like a
very desperate seller

792
00:35:18.113 --> 00:35:20.146
to court a very reluctant buyer.

793
00:35:20.181 --> 00:35:24.491
- [Man] It's the worst
bit. the worst. very worst

794
00:35:24.526 --> 00:35:26.988
bit of management
I've ever seen.

795
00:35:27.023 --> 00:35:28.396
- [Woman] He's won
everything at United.

796
00:35:28.431 --> 00:35:30.365
there's nothing more he can win.

797
00:35:30.400 --> 00:35:32.829
And he's gone from one
world class team to another.

798
00:35:32.864 --> 00:35:34.270
- It may well be a situation.

799
00:35:34.305 --> 00:35:35.799
last game of the
group. for instance.

800
00:35:35.834 --> 00:35:38.604
where. were United
not to win the game

801
00:35:38.639 --> 00:35:39.902
against another rival.

802
00:35:39.937 --> 00:35:41.310
that would allow Real
Madrid to go through.

803
00:35:41.345 --> 00:35:43.037
And I'm not suggesting any
question of impropriety.

804
00:35:43.072 --> 00:35:45.875
but if that happens. certainly
questions will be asked.

805
00:35:45.910 --> 00:35:48.009
And that's the last thing
United need at the moment.

806
00:35:48.044 --> 00:35:49.681
is EUFA on their back.

807
00:35:49.716 --> 00:35:51.111
- Backhanded really. isn't it?

808
00:35:51.146 --> 00:35:52.651
It's all been done
behind everybody's back.

809
00:35:52.686 --> 00:35:53.784
- Beckham never wanted to
leave Manchester United.

810
00:35:53.819 --> 00:35:55.456
I think he was pushed out.

811
00:35:55.491 --> 00:35:58.184
- You don't get the wrong
side of Alex Ferguson.

812
00:35:58.219 --> 00:36:00.120
I mean. that's what
this episode shows.

813
00:36:00.155 --> 00:36:01.990
and it's happened again
and again to players.

814
00:36:02.025 --> 00:36:04.366
If they annoy Ferguson.
they're out the door.

815
00:36:04.401 --> 00:36:07.369
He never speaks to them again.
They have to leave United.

816
00:36:07.404 --> 00:36:09.129
- [Reporter] He might
still be an idol.

817
00:36:09.164 --> 00:36:11.802
but the old colors
are coming down.

818
00:36:11.837 --> 00:36:15.201
In the city where this global
phenomena is a local hero.

819
00:36:15.236 --> 00:36:17.445
they've already started
counting the cost.

820
00:36:17.480 --> 00:36:18.941
- [Man] Everything with
David Beckham on it

821
00:36:18.976 --> 00:36:21.141
probably is the biggest selling
part of Manchester United

822
00:36:21.176 --> 00:36:23.352
merchandise that we do is
the David Beckham range.

823
00:36:23.387 --> 00:36:25.013
- [Reporter] So they'll
feel it when he doesn't play

824
00:36:25.048 --> 00:36:25.783
for them anymore.

825
00:36:25.818 --> 00:36:26.784
- Quite possibly.

826
00:36:26.819 --> 00:36:27.983
I should think it would
be quite substantial.

827
00:36:28.018 --> 00:36:29.589
unless they can get somebody
else in with a very big name.

828
00:36:29.624 --> 00:36:32.295
I think they'll
feel it definitely.

829
00:36:32.330 --> 00:36:35.760
- He went to Real Madrid.
and that was a great move

830
00:36:35.795 --> 00:36:38.565
for him. in the sense of two
of the biggest brand names

831
00:36:38.600 --> 00:36:40.061
in the world.

832
00:36:40.096 --> 00:36:43.273
- Why on earth is it? I
mean. he's only a footballer.

833
00:36:43.308 --> 00:36:45.132
He's a good footballer.
but he is only footballer.

834
00:36:45.167 --> 00:36:46.804
and he's become such a celebrity

835
00:36:46.839 --> 00:36:49.103
that it takes over everything.

836
00:36:49.138 --> 00:36:51.578
- [Reporter] And already.
everyone wants a piece of him.

837
00:36:51.613 --> 00:36:53.646
The hospital today didn't
just do his medical.

838
00:36:53.681 --> 00:36:56.418
It's sponsored it.
and insisted he pose

839
00:36:56.453 --> 00:36:58.046
in front of their logo.

840
00:36:58.081 --> 00:37:00.455
Real spent a lot of money
buying one of the world's

841
00:37:00.490 --> 00:37:02.754
most commercially
valuable sportsmen.

842
00:37:02.789 --> 00:37:04.360
They're going to want
to squeeze every penny

843
00:37:04.395 --> 00:37:07.220
they can from the
Beckham bandwagon.

844
00:37:07.255 --> 00:37:08.496
- [Reporter] Figures
released this month

845
00:37:08.531 --> 00:37:09.992
put their annual
income for last year

846
00:37:10.027 --> 00:37:12.335
at 180.000.000 pounds.

847
00:37:12.370 --> 00:37:14.733
32.000.000 more than
Manchester United.

848
00:37:14.768 --> 00:37:16.933
But they still lag
behind the English club

849
00:37:16.968 --> 00:37:18.374
when selling in Asia.

850
00:37:18.409 --> 00:37:20.068
Putting Beckham on the
books could change that.

851
00:37:20.103 --> 00:37:21.608
- But Manchester
United in the Far East

852
00:37:21.643 --> 00:37:23.775
is just phenomenal. really.

853
00:37:23.810 --> 00:37:25.447
It's very. very. very important.

854
00:37:25.482 --> 00:37:29.484
And in certain ways. we're
four. five. six. seven years

855
00:37:29.519 --> 00:37:31.046
behind Manchester
United in that respect.

856
00:37:31.081 --> 00:37:32.520
You know. Manchester United
have got mega stores.

857
00:37:32.555 --> 00:37:35.556
We've got. you know. little
shops and things like that.

858
00:37:35.591 --> 00:37:37.855
- [Reporter] Real
Madrid shirts are here.

859
00:37:37.890 --> 00:37:39.593
but most are being held back.

860
00:37:39.628 --> 00:37:41.892
the pirates planning
to flood the market

861
00:37:41.927 --> 00:37:44.125
within hours of
Beckham's new number

862
00:37:44.160 --> 00:37:45.830
being announced in Madrid.

863
00:37:45.865 --> 00:37:47.568
(man speaking foreign language)

864
00:37:47.603 --> 00:37:49.064
- [Translator] We have
the shirts in the shops

865
00:37:49.099 --> 00:37:51.341
the day after we
know his new number.

866
00:37:51.376 --> 00:37:53.904
We have to meet the demand
for the Real Madrid kit.

867
00:37:53.939 --> 00:37:57.006
People are already asking.
"Beckham. Beckham. Beckham.

868
00:37:57.041 --> 00:37:58.513
What's his new number?"

869
00:37:58.548 --> 00:38:00.273
(woman speaking
foreign language)

870
00:38:00.308 --> 00:38:02.847
- [Translator] We'll sell
more Real Madrid shirts now.

871
00:38:02.882 --> 00:38:06.818
Beckham is a superstar forever.
All the girls like him.

872
00:38:12.320 --> 00:38:13.627
- [Reporter] There's
little dispute in Japan

873
00:38:13.662 --> 00:38:17.191
over just who is the world's
greatest football star.

874
00:38:17.226 --> 00:38:18.192
- David Beckham.

875
00:38:19.503 --> 00:38:21.162
- [Narrator] It wasn't
long before Madrid

876
00:38:21.197 --> 00:38:23.439
capitalized on their
new star's image.

877
00:38:23.474 --> 00:38:26.508
organizing a pre-season
tour to south Asia.

878
00:38:26.543 --> 00:38:30.842
It is estimated Beckham's
2003 18 day pre-season tour

879
00:38:30.877 --> 00:38:34.681
to Asia earned Madrid
over 10.000.000 Euro.

880
00:38:37.554 --> 00:38:40.489
In 2001. before
Beckham's arrival.

881
00:38:40.524 --> 00:38:44.955
Madrid had a revenue
of 93.2 million pounds.

882
00:38:44.990 --> 00:38:47.925
By 2005. they doubled that.

883
00:38:50.435 --> 00:38:52.963
However. when Beckham
signed for Madrid.

884
00:38:52.998 --> 00:38:55.603
they were a club in a mess.

885
00:38:55.638 --> 00:38:58.936
They were nearly
280.000.000 Euros in debt.

886
00:38:58.971 --> 00:39:01.510
and had become stagnant
in the transfer market.

887
00:39:03.481 --> 00:39:07.175
Club president Florentino
Perez had the perfect answer.

888
00:39:08.882 --> 00:39:12.455
The Galacticos. a group
of high profile players

889
00:39:12.490 --> 00:39:14.248
brought into the
club in an attempt

890
00:39:14.283 --> 00:39:17.526
to create football's
biggest spectacle.

891
00:39:17.561 --> 00:39:20.496
Playing alongside Ronaldo.
Zidane. and Louis Vigo.

892
00:39:20.531 --> 00:39:23.499
Roberto Carlos. Raul.
and Ika Cassius.

893
00:39:23.534 --> 00:39:26.667
Beckham did not require
much time to settle in.

894
00:39:26.702 --> 00:39:29.670
scoring five times in
his first 16 matches

895
00:39:29.705 --> 00:39:31.364
for the Galacticos.

896
00:39:31.399 --> 00:39:34.070
However. despite an
impressive start.

897
00:39:34.105 --> 00:39:37.480
Beckham's time at Madrid didn't
run as smoothly as planned.

898
00:39:37.515 --> 00:39:41.077
with a poor end to
the 2005. 2006 season.

899
00:39:41.112 --> 00:39:43.046
which saw Madrid finish second

900
00:39:43.081 --> 00:39:45.147
to longtime rivals Barcelona.

901
00:39:45.182 --> 00:39:48.590
forcing club president
Florentino Perez to resign.

902
00:39:48.625 --> 00:39:50.284
and big changes were to come.

903
00:39:51.892 --> 00:39:53.089
- [Reporter] Hopefully
you have a thought now

904
00:39:53.124 --> 00:39:54.959
that you could win
this World Cup. David?

905
00:39:54.994 --> 00:39:56.422
- [David] Well. we're not
even thinking about that

906
00:39:56.457 --> 00:39:57.797
at the moment. to be honest.

907
00:39:57.832 --> 00:39:59.062
We let other people do that.

908
00:39:59.097 --> 00:40:00.426
because I'm sure other
people have been getting

909
00:40:00.461 --> 00:40:01.999
sort of carried away with that.

910
00:40:02.034 --> 00:40:03.473
- Brazil is going to
be very difficult.

911
00:40:03.508 --> 00:40:04.771
but if we can do
them. that's it.

912
00:40:04.806 --> 00:40:06.575
- If they can get past
Brazil. they go the whole way.

913
00:40:06.610 --> 00:40:07.906
But obviously that's
a bit of an if.

914
00:40:07.941 --> 00:40:08.973
but there's a good chance.

915
00:40:09.008 --> 00:40:10.172
It's a good chance.

916
00:40:10.207 --> 00:40:11.371
So it we'll be
there in the final-

917
00:40:11.406 --> 00:40:13.076
- Bring on Brazil. Next round.

918
00:40:13.111 --> 00:40:15.144
- The cup's ours. I think.
- Yeah.

919
00:40:15.179 --> 00:40:16.717
- It's coming home.

920
00:40:16.752 --> 00:40:19.346
(upbeat trumpet music)

921
00:40:19.381 --> 00:40:20.688
- [Reporter] If it is Brazil.

922
00:40:20.723 --> 00:40:22.283
it promises to be
an epic encounter.

923
00:40:22.318 --> 00:40:24.527
England have never beaten
them when it matters.

924
00:40:24.562 --> 00:40:28.498
but this is the World Cup. when
you should never say never.

925
00:40:28.533 --> 00:40:30.533
- Well. what we're looking at
is there's three more games

926
00:40:30.568 --> 00:40:31.633
to the World Cup final.

927
00:40:31.668 --> 00:40:35.538
And hopefully. if we can
play like we have done.

928
00:40:35.573 --> 00:40:36.869
then you never know.

929
00:40:36.904 --> 00:40:38.541
- [Reporter] Are we
getting better as a side?

930
00:40:38.576 --> 00:40:40.037
Are you pleased with the
way we're getting better?

931
00:40:40.072 --> 00:40:41.907
- I think we're getting
better and better.

932
00:40:41.942 --> 00:40:46.945
And you see that. when the
comes up. those difficult games.

933
00:40:48.685 --> 00:40:50.113
we are ready.

934
00:40:50.148 --> 00:40:52.720
- [Narrator] After a monumental
win against Argentina.

935
00:40:52.755 --> 00:40:54.887
knocking them out
of the World Cup.

936
00:40:54.922 --> 00:40:57.725
England had a lackluster
remainder of the tournament.

937
00:40:57.760 --> 00:40:59.595
beating Denmark in the last 16

938
00:40:59.630 --> 00:41:03.698
to ultimately be knocked out
by eventual winners. Brazil.

939
00:41:03.733 --> 00:41:06.965
after a catastrophic error
from goalkeeper David Seaman

940
00:41:07.000 --> 00:41:10.199
saw Ronaldinho score
a 40 yard free kick.

941
00:41:10.234 --> 00:41:12.641
- [Reporter] Seaman left
the stadium. still tearful.

942
00:41:12.676 --> 00:41:14.038
without speaking.

943
00:41:14.073 --> 00:41:16.711
But his captain was quick
to jump to his defense.

944
00:41:16.746 --> 00:41:19.142
- I think if he gets
made a scapegoat.

945
00:41:19.177 --> 00:41:20.407
I think it's an
absolute disgrace.

946
00:41:20.442 --> 00:41:23.014
because I think he's
been the best goalkeeper

947
00:41:23.049 --> 00:41:24.279
in this tournament.

948
00:41:24.314 --> 00:41:26.985
and the goal that
they did score.

949
00:41:27.020 --> 00:41:29.152
I feel that it was a fluke goal.

950
00:41:29.187 --> 00:41:32.694
but you know. the Brazilians
are a great players.

951
00:41:32.729 --> 00:41:35.488
And as I said. I hope they go
on to win the tournament now.

952
00:41:35.523 --> 00:41:36.764
- Dave is a world class keeper.

953
00:41:36.799 --> 00:41:37.996
No one's putting
the blame on him

954
00:41:38.031 --> 00:41:39.327
or any of the other players.

955
00:41:39.362 --> 00:41:40.768
You know. it's just
one of them things.

956
00:41:40.803 --> 00:41:43.001
- I wouldn't put any
blame on David Seaman.

957
00:41:43.036 --> 00:41:44.739
or any goalkeeper
that that happened to.

958
00:41:44.774 --> 00:41:46.169
I've never seen a corner
kick taken like that.

959
00:41:46.204 --> 00:41:48.644
It was whipped with
more pace and accuracy

960
00:41:48.679 --> 00:41:49.645
than I've ever seen.

961
00:41:49.680 --> 00:41:51.845
- David is a fantastic
professional.

962
00:41:51.880 --> 00:41:55.277
You know. he's been there
for England over the years.

963
00:41:55.312 --> 00:41:57.851
and made fantastic saves
for club and country.

964
00:41:59.118 --> 00:42:01.316
- What can you say? I
think we deserved it.

965
00:42:01.351 --> 00:42:02.185
- We'll be back.

966
00:42:02.220 --> 00:42:03.186
- What are we going to do?

967
00:42:03.221 --> 00:42:05.254
- We'll win the Euros.

968
00:42:05.289 --> 00:42:07.795
- [Reporter] They burnt
a Brazilian shirt.

969
00:42:07.830 --> 00:42:09.665
cheered as if England had won.

970
00:42:11.196 --> 00:42:14.769
For others. silent thoughts
and soft words of consolation.

971
00:42:14.804 --> 00:42:16.529
- [Reporter] So. as the
team kit was being loaded

972
00:42:16.564 --> 00:42:17.937
this evening for
the flight home.

973
00:42:17.972 --> 00:42:20.808
Sven-Goran Eriksson spoke
of how he's told his players

974
00:42:20.843 --> 00:42:22.678
to think of the future.

975
00:42:22.713 --> 00:42:25.681
- I told them that I
think 90. 95% of you

976
00:42:25.716 --> 00:42:26.682
sitting here today.

977
00:42:28.543 --> 00:42:30.620
very sad with the head downs.

978
00:42:30.655 --> 00:42:33.821
You have a big chance to be
in it in four years' time.

979
00:42:36.419 --> 00:42:37.759
- [Narrator] Four years later.

980
00:42:37.794 --> 00:42:40.762
the England squad set
off to the 2006 World Cup

981
00:42:40.797 --> 00:42:42.159
with high hopes.

